  calories: 609 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  carbohydrates: 90 g
  protein: 19 g
  fiber: 13 g
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Cook the quinoa: bring @water{1 1/2%cups}, the @red quinoa{3/4%cup}, and a large pinch of
@salt{} to a boil in a #small pot{}. Once boiling, cover and reduce to a simmer for
~{15%minutes}, until tender.

Chop the @tarragon{1%sprig} leaves and discard the stems. Halve and juice the
@lemon{1}. Using a #vegetable peeler{}, peel the @rainbow carrots{1%bunch}, then shave
into ribbons, rotating as necessary. Trim, quarter, and core the @fennel{1}, then slice
as thinly as possible.

Make the shaved vegetable salad: place both the fennel and carrots in a #medium bowl{}
and toss with @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and the lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

Candy the pistachios: heat a #small non-stick pan{} over medium heat. Add the
@pistachios{1%ounce} and cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until toasted and fragrant.
Add @water{1%tablespoon} and @sugar{1%tablespoon} to the pan, swirling continuously,
until pistachios are coated with a syrupy glaze. Remove from pan and season with @salt{}.

> Watch the pan carefully! Sugar can burn quickly.

Make the tarragon crema: in a #small bowl{}, combine the @sour cream{4%tablespoon},
@red wine vinegar{1%tablespoon}, and tarragon. Season with @salt{} and @ground black
pepper{}.

Plate the quinoa and top with the carrots and fennel. Dollop with the tarragon crema
and sprinkle with candied pistachios. Enjoy!